Hey Markus,

I am curious what you find when you get back from vacation. As far as I
know we haven&#39;t run into that at IA using either Oracle or Openjdk 7.

FetchHTTP has a setting sslTrustLevel which by default is &quot;open&quot;, which
means &quot;trust all certs including expired, selfsigned, and those for which
we do not have a CA&quot;. Maybe you have it configured stricter? Even so, only
the affected urls should fail, the crawl should not stop.

Noah



